From: Dr. Kenny L. Samui <KSamui@vet.unza.zm>

>From experience, I doubt it! I do not think that anyone would find RIG in
our public health institutions. Post exposure treatment in Zambia
especially, is usually composed of anti tetanus, antibiotics (if the bite
wound is severe) and post-exposure vaccination.
